@NODE Intro "Introduction"

                                  ..
                             .---:  :---------.
                             |   ····         |
                            [%] iNTRODUCTiON [%]
                             |         ....   |
                             `---------:  :---'
                                        ··

A  small  CLI  utility  for  sysops  that  goes  through  a directory on the
         hard-drive and the relevant bbs file listing and outputs:

	· duplicate entries in the directory listing
	· files in the listing but not on the hard-drive
	· files on the hard-drive but not in the listing

These are output to the cli window as standard and leaves it up to you as to
whether  you  want  to  remove  it.   Basically this was created to clean up
directories on a BBS because we'd had a couple of duplicate files sneak past
us  on  13th  Hour  due  to old files being deleted by mistake or duplicates
                    popping up when they weren't wanted.

This  version is approximately 3 times faster than version 1.00 so obviously
we  recommend  this  one  instead :) On a test listing of one meg it took 10
seconds  to  check  and output all relevant information, while version v1.00
                              took 27 seconds.
@ENDNODE
@NODE Install "Installation"

                                  ..
                             .---:  :---------.
                             |   ····         |
                            [%] iNSTALLATiON [%]
                             |         ....   |
                             `---------:  :---'
                                        ··

Just  copy  this  to  any  directory  you  store  your bbs utilities and run
whenever  you  wish.  There are two versions, a standard version and the 020
version. Rename the command to "dirchecker" and put it wherever. Simple eh?
@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage "Usage"

                               ..
                          .---:  :--------------.
                          |   ····              |
                         [%] USiNG THE PROGRAM [%]
                          |              ....   |
                          `--------------:  :---'
                                          ··

Open a shell window and type:

                          dirchecker <dir> <list>

Dir is the directory on the hard-drive you wish to check.
List is the listing on the hard-drive you wish to check.

If you run dirchecker without any parameters it will tell you that parameters
          are required and give a quick rundown of how to use it.
@ENDNODE
